&quot;On the 'Belt and Road initiative'? We're, listen, we're very enthusiastic about the 'Belt and Road initiative', we're very interested in the...what... President Xi is doing. And don't forget that the United Kingdom was the first country to sign up to the Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank. We are the first country. So we are very pro-China.&quot;<br />
<br />
&quot;We are the most open economy in Europe. Don't forget, the most open to international investment, particularly Chinese investment. We have Chinese companies coming in to do... Hinkley, for instance, the big nuclear power plant. So we're very enthusiastic, and... there you go.&quot;
